## C4. Demonstrate understanding of structured teaching practices (Rationale) (20%)

### HD
Exceptionally synthesises and evaluates explicit instruction, modelling, and scaffolding approaches to support learner development. Exceptionally reflective discussion with connections between experiences, and developmental theory.

### D
Distinctly synthesises and evaluates explicit instruction, modelling, and scaffolding approaches to support learner development. Distinctive reflection with connections to developmental theory.

### C
Clearly explains explicit instruction, modelling, and scaffolding approaches to support learner development. Clear reflection evident with connections to theory.

### P
Describes explicit instruction, modelling, and scaffolding approaches to support learner development. Reflects on experiences with some theoretical links.

### F
Does not adequately describe explicit instruction, modelling, and scaffolding approaches to support learner development. No reflection on experiences. No links to theory.

